Preconditions:
The method should take two parameters: an integer n representing the number of taps in the garden, and an array of integers ranges representing the range of each tap.
The ranges array should have a length equal to n.
The ranges array should contain only positive integers.

Postconditions:
The method should return an integer representing the minimum number of taps that should be open to water the whole garden.
If the garden cannot be watered, the method should return -1.